The paper deals with the mathematical analysis of evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves probability theory and stochastic processes, which are relevant to the categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents results on tail bounds and fitness level theorems, which are related to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
